        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 7:46PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 746 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles northwest of Manchester, or 22 miles northwest of Clarksville,
moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Manchester, Valliant, Millerton, Garvin, Redland, Silver City,
Kiomatia, Farmers Hill and Kanawha.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
